At any rate, Brutas, I am saying that Christians are morally week in that they (not the non-believer) never fully accept responsibility for their actions.<br>
<br>
There is alot of complex answers to your points.  I'll try my best to share my point of view for this.(formating problems)<br>
<br>
Ok I'll start by adressing the difference between nature and conscience(or, humankind).  Space and Time exist, Thats a given.  Space is an environment where 'things' take place.  In our need for order we define those process' that take place within space as 'time'.  Space and Time, for the most part are more easily nderstood because they are relatively constant.  Its relatively constant because the 'things' that take place are a result of organisms that are 'bound' by nature.  These 'things' that take place, or events, react to their environment(space) according to their inherent survival mechanism.  Balance is obtained by species counteracting each other.  Basically, the organisms have no choice in the matter.  They react and act according to survival.  <br>
<br>
  Humans are not bound completly by nature because we have a choice.  That 'choice' throws a wrench into the space and time process.  We can choose to do something totally irrational.  Generally we don't.  But sometimes we do.  Entertainment is a great example of this.  Choose to play EQ or go to work.  I know there is a possibility that I can be fired which can jeopardize shelter and food for me.  But fuk=it, I wanna play.  <br>
<br>
  When we make a choice, space and time reacts upon our 'event'.  Space and time react to all events but the difference is that we have the ability to manipulate space and time on a conscious level, whether that level be rational or irrational.  <br>
<br>
  Ughh I hope this doesn't get ugly.  Space and time can also be compared to order and chaos.  In many ways, truth and love can be compared also.  The difference once again, is choice.  Space and time/order and chaos do not have a choice.  They always attempt balance.  Sometimes that balance takes 6 billion years and other times it takes a nanosecond.  But either way, the event takes place.  <br>
<br>
  Ok now back to the idea of 'the forbidden fruit'.  Ok lets pretend that God really is Alpha and omega.  I don't believe that God played the 'life' game and used all the cheat-codes.  Some people say, &quot;he is omnipotent&quot;.   God has feelings just like we do.  IMO, he did the 'life' thing as we are doing.  But God basically said( to Adam and Eve), &quot;Ok let us enjoy life together, and all the feelings, thoughts, events and everything else that comes along with it&quot;  (We were created for friendship)  <br>
<br>
  We had free-will at that time, but God did not create a violent, dark world for us.  That doesn't mean we had no challenges.  It didn't mean that we were to pick berries and fruit and shit all day long.  The change came when we Chose to bite the forbidden fruit.  The forbiden fruit was not a temptation.  It existed because we have free-will.  How could we have free-will if everything was not an option.  <br>
<br>
  By making that 'choice', we became part of a world where we found ourselves bound by nature, with the exception of the same old guarentee, free-will.  We chose to relive what God had already relived because we wanted that knowledge too.  Does an escaped concentration camp mother choose to send here baby into the camp so he can know what its like?  Hell no, because she loves her baby.  God, just like any loving mother or father, chose to create a world, or environment condusive for love ad truth.  But since we wanted to try it all for ourselves, we got it.   With this new 'knowledge' came experience and with experience came the inbalance of love and truth.  We had never earned truth or love so we had to attain it for ourselves now.  (ok now this is gettin gugly)<br>
<br>
Sorry if this is getting to messy.  So now humakind is still trying to understand 'life'.  In all ways.  Eventually, the path will lead us back to truth and love.  But how can one find truth all alone if God is there to help them?  Just as we have a choice, God does too.  Something similar to the opening of another dimension, God can choose to intervene, usually by way of love.  <br>
<br>
Do people feel like they literally chose just as Adam and Eve did?  No.  Did I choose to live in a dysfunctional family.  Hell no.  Same kind of shit.  Howver, there is still an open-line of communication with God.  IMO, anyone can speak with him.  You do not have to be 'saved' to communicate with God.  But ultimately, God will come to his children and offer safe haven, or salvation.  Some children might not choose this.  Eventually, the lives of communication will be severed and 'hell' will take place.  Hell, to me is a life without communication with God.  Since the form of communication with God is truth and love, some people will be fuked, quite frankly.  <br>
<br>
Quote:At any rate, Brutas, I am saying that Christians are morally week in that they (not the non-believer) never fully accept responsibility for their actions.<br>
<br>
The full brunt of life without God can over power the individual.  God knows that and will love us when we need his love.  Life as we know it is what we asked for.  I believe it is possible for someone Very Stoic to learn much from his actions.  But I don't believe anyone person has the ability to learn everything of the consequences of his actions.  Impossible.  In retrospect, which is an attempt of stopping time, allows us to realize many things.  But we are too limited and specialized to be able to comprehend the results of our actions.  On a social level we have a much better chance, but through 'history repeating itself' we can see that doens't work either.  In the extreme case, I can see what you mean.  But love makes that possible, not truth.  God can choose as well. He has free-will.  I would agree that it is not possible if we were bound by nature, but we are not.<br>
<br>
Quote Lurikeen:  After all, they became Christians to escape the mental anguish associated with their behavior.<br>
<br>
  Not necasarily.  You are a good example of this.  You seek truth more than the average Joe.  A lot more actually.  You have the potential to seek truth for a long ass time.  Under the right circumstances.  But you would have to keep the validity of feelings and love at bay as it will constantly be surging with the truth you discover.  Hence, more shitty things will probably happen in response to your seeking of truth.  For the most part, you get what you ask for.  Eventually the truth will over power you and you will recognize love as equal to truth.  Thats just my opinion.  Please don't take it as negative as you well know that I have much respect for you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    In more colorful terms, when seeking truth, one must intertwine their new found knowledge of truth with love in order to create balance(as is similar with space and time)  but if you keep digging a cave in search of truth, you will take it in the ass because, just like space and time are creating balance, truth and love do as well.  The reaction you 'feel' when you take it in the ass might not feel 'fair' but under the post-fruit reality, neither are your gains in the arena of truth.  <br>
